Large size. Colouration light pale green to yellowish (Fig. 
1T
). Head short, narrow with dark brown ocelli (Fig. 
3I
). Pronotum flat, concave posteriorly (Fig. 
5J
). Elytra, transparent, extending to 2/3 of abdomen. Wings rounded, broad, with condensed irregular veins (Fig. 
10G
). Legs same colour as body. Femora long, thin, slightly wider at anterior and compressed at posterior. Posterior tibia thin, slender, armed with 21 external and three medio-internal spines (Fig. 
7F
). Abdomen pale yellowish. Ovipositor short. Cerci long with pointed ends (Fig. 
1T
).

Ohio, Franklin, New Jersey, Washington, Pakistan (
Cigliano et al. 2020
).
